10th October 2008                                    Claws Mail 3.6.1

		    CLAWS MAIL  RELEASE NOTES
                    http://www.claws-mail.org
		      
Claws Mail is a GTK+ based, user-friendly, lightweight, and fast 
email client.

Notes for this release:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Claws Mail now requires libetpan 0.57 for IMAP and NNTP.

* SSL support is now provided by gnuTLS exclusively. OpenSSL support
  has been dropped due to licensing issues.

New in this release:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* Added /View/Fullscreen option.

* Re-ordering of the filtering/processing condition and actions lists
  is now possible using drag'n'drop.

* Updated Brazilian Portuguese and French translations.

* Bug fixes:
	o bug 1737, 'Claws-Mail 3.6.0-1 crashes upon opening.'
		    (MAEMO)
	o bug 1742, 'Attachment list contents not visible/scrollable'
		    (MAEMO)
	o bug 1747, 'Wanderlust keybindings no longer working
		    (regression)'
	o bug 1749, 'Shortcut keys for color labels not changeable'
	o fix failure of Hide toolbar option on restart.

For further details of the numbered bugs listed above consult
http://www.thewildbeast.co.uk/claws-mail/bugzilla/index.cgi

---------------------------------------------------------------------
See ChangeLog for full information regarding changes in this release.
